but l didn't want any part of that in my life.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.724
You know, l kept waiting for more field time,

21:49.892 --> 21:51.768
and he didn't like it
if l went in the field by myself

21:51.852 --> 21:54.479
'cause he wanted to go so bad.
He didn't want me to go.

21:54.730 --> 21:56.815
-(POWER TOOLS WHlRRlNG)
-(HAMMERlNG)

22:07.827 --> 22:09.786
PETER: We got Sue back to Hill City.

22:09.870 --> 22:12.914
We moved the big blocks
into the warehouse,

22:12.999 --> 22:17.043
actually built a room
around where we had put Sue.

22:17.128 --> 22:19.087
Started working on this wonderful fossil.

22:21.549 --> 22:22.841
WENTZ: When I was prepping Sue,

22:22.925 --> 22:26.636
I was cloistered like a monk
in the back corner of the back building.

22:26.721 --> 22:29.264
Doing preparation, you just...
"Just leave me alone," right?

22:29.348 --> 22:32.600
But everybody was in there.
There would be school kids in there.

22:33.144 --> 22:34.769
Or another day, there'd be

22:35.271 --> 22:38.023
some scientist guys coming along in there.

22:38.107 --> 22:39.607
l mean, Pete had, like, 30 scientists

22:39.692 --> 22:42.569
working on a major new monograph
on Tyrannosaurus rex,

22:42.653 --> 22:45.363
so you got to suck it up.
Pete wants it this way.

22:45.448 --> 22:48.074
He wants this specimen
available to everybody.

22:48.159 --> 22:49.868
lt was so beautiful.

22:49.952 --> 22:54.622
Just the preservation was incredible.
lt was just, "Wow."

22:54.707 --> 22:56.207
Everybody knew about Sue.

22:56.417 --> 22:59.544
We hadn't made any secret of the fact
that we'd collected her.

22:59.628 --> 23:02.380
PETER: We had 2,000 visitors
sign this little guest book

23:02.465 --> 23:05.925
that went way in the back in our warehouse
to see the skull of Sue.

23:06.635 --> 23:09.179
CURRIE: l was just totally flabbergasted
when l saw the specimen.

23:09.263 --> 23:11.556
First of all, the size is just so imposing,

23:11.640 --> 23:13.391
but what l was more amazed by

23:13.476 --> 23:16.144
was what a greatjob
they were doing preparing the specimen.

23:16.228 --> 23:19.147
BlLL HARLAN: l'd heard inklings
that the Black Hills Institute

23:19.231 --> 23:20.774
boys had found something.

23:20.983 --> 23:26.404
One of the first things l saw was actually,
you know, part of the skull of Sue

23:26.489 --> 23:28.740
still encased in matrix.

23:28.824 --> 23:31.201
Sixty-five million years later,

23:31.285 --> 23:33.953
this animal really had the power
to give you goose bumps.

23:34.038 --> 23:36.122
To see the look
on Pete's face and Neal's face.

23:36.207 --> 23:38.083
Those guys were just like proud papas.

23:38.167 --> 23:40.919
They would inform you. They would
go do classes at school for the kids,

23:41.003 --> 23:44.172
so it was very educational for all of us.
l learned a lot from that.

23:52.014 --> 23:55.600
PETER: Eversince we created
that little museum on our parents' ranch,

23:55.684 --> 23:58.561
it's always been our dream
to have a museum here in Hill City.

24:00.106 --> 24:04.651
And finding Sue the Tyrannosaurus rex,
here's the anchor for the museum.

24:06.904 --> 24:08.613
The whole town is behind us.

24:08.697 --> 24:10.615
It's going to put Hill City on the map

24:10.699 --> 24:13.034
in a way that it's never
been on the map before.

24:15.996 --> 24:18.790
Didn't matter how many
other projects we had going on.

24:18.874 --> 24:21.417
With Sue, Sue took precedence.

24:24.421 --> 24:27.590
PETER: We found out all kinds
of cool things about this dinosaur.

24:27.675 --> 24:29.968
Broken and healed bones
all over the skeleton.

24:30.052 --> 24:33.388
This animal had a terrible life,
a terrible, rough life.

24:35.224 --> 24:37.350
The skull of Sue actually had...

24:37.560 --> 24:41.521
The left side of the lowerjaw
had been literally ripped out of the socket,

24:41.605 --> 24:43.398
still held together here at the symphysis,

24:43.482 --> 24:45.900
where the two ends of the lowerjaw
come together in the front,

24:46.026 --> 24:48.236
but it's been torn loose from the socket,

24:48.404 --> 24:50.280
which allows the jaw to open and close.

24:50.364 --> 24:52.448
And the postorbital,
the bone directly behind the eye,

24:52.533 --> 24:56.786
was broken and pulled outwards
and laying at sort of a weird angle.

24:57.329 --> 25:01.749
So I think that she actually died from
the attack ofanotherTyrannosaurus rex.

25:07.965 --> 25:09.591
WENTZ: That was a bigjob.

25:09.675 --> 25:12.510
l mean, it took me a year, literally a year,

25:12.595 --> 25:16.848
just to remove individual bones
from around the skull, and then...

25:17.516 --> 25:21.686
And then to take that, the giant hip bones,
off of the nose.

25:26.192 --> 25:29.944
PETER: We finally were able
to lift the pelvis off of Sue's skull

25:30.029 --> 25:31.863
in the beginning of May 1 992.

25:31.947 --> 25:33.489
Okay. Let's go.

25:33.574 --> 25:35.325
-Up?
-Let's go.

25:39.622 --> 25:45.793
WENTZ: Taking that hip off of Sue's skull
was critical to doing it right

